com.pump.data

Interface BeanMapConverter<K,B>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of bean identifier
    B - the type of bean wrapper object this converter creates/reads. In its simplest form, a BeanConverter may simply interact the map of key/value pairs, so B may just be Map. But if you want to create a separate object for a Person or ProductOrder or Address: this interface lets you do that (so long as there are distinguishing characteristics in either the bean ID or the map of data that will inform you which type of object to use).

    public interface BeanMapConverter<K,B>
    This converts a map of key/value pairs into a bean object and back again.

    • Method Detail

      • createBean

        B createBean(K beanId,
             java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> beanData)
        Create a bean representation from a collection key/value pairs, the bean id, and the branch that is creating this object.

        This needs to be a relatively light/fast call, because it may be consulted frequently.

        Parameters:
        source - the branch that supplied this data.
        beanId - the id of the bean requested.
        beanData - a map of key/value pairs that represent this bean's data.
        Returns:
        an object representing this bean.

      • getData

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> getData(K beanId,
                                                         B beanData)
        Convert a bean object into a map of key/value pairs.
        Parameters:
        beanId - the id of the bean argument.
        beanData - the object from which we'll extract key/value pairs.
        Returns:
        a map of key/value pairs that represent that data in this bean.
